<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
	<LanguageData>
		<!-- EN: canning -->
		<VCE_Canning.label>装罐</VCE_Canning.label>
		<!-- EN: Canning is a method of preserving food in which the food contents are processed and sealed in an airtight container (jars like Mason jars, and steel and tin cans). Canning provides a shelf life of several years. A freeze-dried canned product, such as canned dried lentils, could last as long as 30 years in an edible state. This research gives access to the canning machine. -->
		<VCE_Canning.description>将食物密封在容器内来更好地保存食物。罐装食物能有数年的保质期。该研究允许建造装罐机。</VCE_Canning.description>
		<!-- EN:
			<li>subject->the vaults of flavor</li>
			<li>subject_story->revolutionized food preservation through canning, extending the bounty of the harvest</li>
			<li>subject_story->mastered the science of sealing freshness and taste, ensuring nourishment year-round</li>
			<li>subject_story->introduced the canning machine, a key to unlocking the potential of prolonged food storage</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->preserving the essence of the seasons within every jar and can</li>
		-->
		<VCE_Canning.generalRules.rulesStrings>
			<li>subject->味觉避难所</li>
			<li>subject_story->用罐头革新食物储存技术，让收获的果实得以保存长久</li>
			<li>subject_story->掌握用科学方法封装新鲜食材，让它在数年后仍能保存营养</li>
			<li>subject_story->发明了装罐机，让人可以批量将食物入库</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->在罐头中保存每一丝食材该有的味道</li>
		</VCE_Canning.generalRules.rulesStrings>
		
		<!-- EN: cheese making -->
		<VCE_CheeseMaking.label>奶酪制作</VCE_CheeseMaking.label>
		<!-- EN: Cheesemaking (or caseiculture) is the craft of making cheese. The production of cheese, like many other food preservation processes, allows the nutritional and economic value of milk to be preserved in concentrated form. Cheesemaking allows the production of the cheese with diverse flavors and consistencies. This research gives access to the cheese press. -->
		<VCE_CheeseMaking.description>制作奶酪的手艺。将原乳制成奶酪能浓缩它的营养价值。制作出的奶酪味道和浓度各异。该科技允许建造奶酪压制器。</VCE_CheeseMaking.description>
		<!-- EN:
			<li>subject->alchemy of milk</li>
			<li>subject_story->transformed the humble origins of milk into the rich complexity of cheese</li>
			<li>subject_story->cultivated an array of cheeses, each a testament to the craft and culture of cheesemaking</li>
			<li>subject_story->designed the cheese press, squeezing out new traditions and tastes from an ancient practice</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->crafting cultures and flavors in the artful creation of cheese</li>
		-->
		<VCE_CheeseMaking.generalRules.rulesStrings>
			<li>subject->牛奶炼金术</li>
			<li>subject_story->将廉价的牛奶加工成精致的奶酪</li>
			<li>subject_story->量产了堆积如山的奶酪，精进这一古老工艺</li>
			<li>subject_story->设计出了奶酪压制器，从老祖宗的指挥里榨出浓厚的风味</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->在奶酪这一惊奇发明中挥洒高雅的味道</li>
		</VCE_CheeseMaking.generalRules.rulesStrings>
		
		<!-- EN: food condiments -->
		<VCE_CondimentsResearch.label>食物调料</VCE_CondimentsResearch.label>
		<!-- EN: A condiment is a spice, sauce, or preparation that is added to food, either after or during cooking, to impart a specific flavor, to enhance the flavor, or to complement the dish. All condiments are created at the condiment prep table. -->
		<VCE_CondimentsResearch.description>香料，酱料或药剂一类的调料，在烹饪前或后加入，用来调整，强化或辅助风味。所有调料都需在调料制备台制作。</VCE_CondimentsResearch.description>
		<!-- EN:
			<li>subject->flavors of distinction</li>
			<li>subject_story->unlocked the secrets of enhancing flavor through the creation of diverse condiments</li>
			<li>subject_story->pioneered the use of herbs, spices, and sauces to transform simple meals into culinary experiences</li>
			<li>subject_story->cultivated a rich culture of taste, encouraging culinary experimentation and innovation</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->elevating the art of flavor through condiment mastery</li>
		-->
		<VCE_CondimentsResearch.generalRules.rulesStrings>
			<li>subject->异来之香</li>
			<li>subject_story->通过制作一连串的调料打开通往新味道的大门</li>
			<li>subject_story->创新地用草药，香料和酱汁将普普通通的食物变成独一无二的工艺品</li>
			<li>subject_story->创造出丰富的各式风味，给了厨师们一片可以肆意开拓的新大陆</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->熟用调料，将烹饪之艺提升到全新境界</li>
		</VCE_CondimentsResearch.generalRules.rulesStrings>
		
		<!-- EN: deep frying -->
		<VCE_DeepFrying.label>油炸</VCE_DeepFrying.label>
		<!-- EN: Deep frying (also referred to as deep fat frying) is a cooking method in which food is submerged in hot fat, most commonly oil, as opposed to the shallow oil used in conventional frying done in a frying pan. This research gives access to the deep fryer. -->
		<VCE_DeepFrying.description>油炸是将食物放进大量油之中的一种烹饪方式。该研究允许建造油锅。</VCE_DeepFrying.description>
		<!-- EN:
			<li>subject->the golden crunch</li>
			<li>subject_story->discovered the transformative effect of deep frying, enveloping foods in a crispy, golden exterior</li>
			<li>subject_story->engineered the deep fryer, a marvel of culinary technology, to achieve consistent and perfect results</li>
			<li>subject_story->elevated the simple act of frying into a culinary craft, celebrated across cultures</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->delving into the depths of flavor with the magic of deep frying</li>
		-->
		<VCE_DeepFrying.generalRules.rulesStrings>
			<li>subject->唇齿间的黄金</li>
			<li>subject_story->发现了油炸这种革命性的烹调方法，可以把任何食材炸到酥脆金黄</li>
			<li>subject_story->打造出了油炸锅，烹饪史上的奇迹，可以大量产出全新的油炸产品</li>
			<li>subject_story->将简单的元素融合成一种举世皆爱的味道</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->用油炸法探明烹饪之艺的全新深度</li>
		</VCE_DeepFrying.generalRules.rulesStrings>
		
		<!-- EN: grilling -->
		<VCE_Grilling.label>烧烤</VCE_Grilling.label>
		<!-- EN: Grilling is a form of cooking that involves dry heat applied to the surface of food, commonly from above, below or from the side. Grilling usually involves a significant amount of direct, radiant heat, and tends to be used for cooking meat and vegetables quickly. This research gives access to the grill. -->
		<VCE_Grilling.description>烤是一种烹饪方式，用干火从四周烧灼食物。烤制食物时会放出大量热量，所以可以快速烹制肉和菜。该研究允许建造烤架。</VCE_Grilling.description>
		<!-- EN:
			<li>subject->the primal art of fire</li>
			<li>subject_story->embraced the primal connection between fire and food, perfecting the technique of grilling</li>
			<li>subject_story->transformed the act of cooking into a celebration of flavor, texture, and aroma</li>
			<li>subject_story->innovated with designs for grills that enhance the natural qualities of meats and vegetables</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->searing perfection into every meal with the mastery of grilling</li>
		-->
		<VCE_Grilling.generalRules.rulesStrings>
			<li>subject->火与肉的最初羁绊</li>
			<li>subject_story->追忆起火与食物的初次见面，将烤肉的魅力再次发掘</li>
			<li>subject_story->将简单的食材烤出有层次感的味道</li>
			<li>subject_story->用天然的手法结合肉与蔬菜，创造出了全新的烧烤菜式</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->用烧烤的技艺丰富每一张餐桌</li>
		</VCE_Grilling.generalRules.rulesStrings>
		
		<!-- EN: soup cooking -->
		<VCE_SoupCooking.label>炖汤</VCE_SoupCooking.label>
		<!-- EN: Soup is a primarily liquid food, generally served warm or hot, that is made by combining ingredients of meat or vegetables with stock, or water. Hot soups are additionally characterized by boiling solid ingredients in liquids in a pot until the flavors are extracted. This research also gives access to the electric pot necessary to cook soups. -->
		<VCE_SoupCooking.description>汤是肉和菜在水里熬制成的温热液态食物。热汤必须在锅内被持续熬制直到所有味道都分解出来。该研究会允许建造炖汤必不可少的电汤锅。</VCE_SoupCooking.description>
		<!-- EN:
			<li>subject->the essence of nourishment</li>
			<li>subject_story->mastered the delicate balance of ingredients to create soups that comfort and heal</li>
			<li>subject_story->introduced the electric pot, revolutionizing soup preparation with efficiency and precision</li>
			<li>subject_story->expanded the culinary repertoire, exploring the depths of flavor achievable in liquid form</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->crafting the soul of cuisine in every pot of soup</li>
		-->
		<VCE_SoupCooking.generalRules.rulesStrings>
			<li>subject->营养的精华</li>
			<li>subject_story->学会了将精细配比的食材煮成暖人身心的汤</li>
			<li>subject_story->引进了电煮锅，极大地提升了炖汤的效率</li>
			<li>subject_story->增加了菜式多样性，让液体能拥有它独特的味道</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->煮出一锅锅烹饪的灵魂</li>
		</VCE_SoupCooking.generalRules.rulesStrings>

		<!-- EN: stew cooking -->
		<VCE_StewCooking.label>炖菜</VCE_StewCooking.label>
		<!-- EN: Stew is a form of a very nourishing meal, cooked in bulk over fire. This research also gives access to the wood-fired pot necessary to cook stews. -->
		<VCE_StewCooking.description>炖菜是一种非常滋补的食物，在火上批量熬制而成。该研究允许建造炖菜必不可少的燃料炖锅。</VCE_StewCooking.description>
		<!-- EN:
			<li>subject->hearth and heart</li>
			<li>subject_story->embraced the tradition of stew cooking, bringing together community and cuisine over the warmth of a shared pot</li>
			<li>subject_story->cultivated techniques to craft stews that are not only nourishing but carry the flavors of cultural heritage and togetherness</li>
			<li>subject_story->introduced the wood-fired pot, an essential tool for preparing these hearty meals in the traditional way</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->nurturing bodies and souls with the communal art of stew making</li>
		-->
		<VCE_StewCooking.generalRules.rulesStrings>
			<li>subject->炉与心</li>
			<li>subject_story->复兴了传统的炖菜，让街坊邻居可以聚到炉子前吃大锅饭</li>
			<li>subject_story->学会了烧出非同一般的炖菜，不炖出营养还能炖出团结</li>
			<li>subject_story->引进了木柴炖锅，用传统的方法烹饪这种用心的食物</li>
			<li>subject_gerund->在其乐融融的氛围中充实身心</li>
		</VCE_StewCooking.generalRules.rulesStrings>
		<!-- EN: soybean fermentation -->
		<VCE_SoyFermentation.label>大豆发酵</VCE_SoyFermentation.label>
		<!-- EN: Soybean fermentation is the process by which soybeans are submitted to a chemical breakdown by bacteria, yeasts, or other microorganisms, transforming into new products. This research gives access to the soy sauce fermenter. -->
		<VCE_SoyFermentation.description>大豆发酵是指大豆被细菌、酵母或其他微生物进行化学分解，转化为新产品的过程。本研究为酱油发酵罐的研制提供了途径。</VCE_SoyFermentation.description>
		
	</LanguageData>
